            . I am assistant to my father, James Frost, who is a <rs id="t18180218-79-viclabel414" type="occupation">brass-founder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-79-victim508 t18180218-79-viclabel414"></join>-the prisoner worked for us. On the 3rd of February, about seven o'clock, I watched the prisoner, and saw him put six pounds of copper into his pocket; I stopped him, and told him I suspected him; he said, he had none. I said, I must search him; he then said, he would give it to me-which he did; it was between his shirt and skin.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I beg for mercy.</p>
